article.headline: Valparaiso 78, North Park 47
article.story: VALPARAISO, Ind. -- Howard Little scored 16 points and Urule Igbavboa had 15 as Valparaiso beat North Park 78-47 Tuesday night. Erik Buggs scored 10, including 2-of-2 from the three-point line, and Cameron Witt had 10 off the bench as the Crusaders (4-9) shot 53.2 percent from the field. Phil Schniedermeider led North Park with 12, including 5-of-6 from the field. Clayton Cahill scored 11 for the Vikings (8-3). Valparaiso outrebounded the Vikings 31-23 and outscored the Vikings 48-18 in the paint. Valpo scored 36 points off turnovers, compared with 9 for North Park. The Vikings shot 45 percent from the field. North Park made 6 of 11 free throws, compared with 4-of-5 for Valparaiso.
